headline: Nvidia's Huang Says on Track to Make Half-Trillion Dollars of AI Technology By 2029
summary: Nvidia founder and CEO Jensen Huang says Friday's unveiling of a U.S.-made Blackwell wafer to make artificial intelligence chips domestically was "just the beginning."  The wafer was made at Taiwan Semiconductor's facility in Arizona.  "TSMC is an incredible partner in -- a strategic partner for United States and in bringing manufacturing of the most -- in most critical sector of technology here to United States," Huang told Fox News' The Sunday Briefing.

headline: How Investors May Respond To Amcor (AMCR) CFO Transition and Launch of Healthcare Packaging Solution
summary: Amcor plc recently appointed Stephen R. Scherger as its new Chief Financial Officer, following the retirement announcement of Michael Casamento, while also reaffirming its earnings guidance and launching the AmSecure healthcare packaging solution.
